    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "If i understand correctly, @TomAugspurger you are (in today's terms) just suggesting that ``is_extension_type`` should return ``True`` if ``is_extension_array_dtype`` does, right? (Notice this is already true for ``Categorical``).\r\n\r\nThen I think the only two hardcoded types would be ``datetimetz`` and ``sparse``.\r\n\r\nBy the way: is there any plan to make those extension types too? The fact that\r\n```\r\nIn [2]: s = pd.date_range(start='2010-08-08', end='2010-08-09', tz='utc')\r\n\r\nIn [3]: s._values is s\r\nOut[3]: True\r\n```\r\nis quite annoying in parts of the code like this:\r\nhttps://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/blob/ffae158749c9b72720a7fe3295d323082a5fe420/pandas/core/base.py#L942\r\n\r\nwhich assume that the ``_values`` of an ``Index`` are not an ``Index`` themselves."
  },
